canonical:
  title: 上慶尙安撫使崔司成滋賀正狀
  author: 金之岱
  language: lzh
  text: 雞人報曉爭糊楚戶之鷄鳳詔頒春催浴荀池之鳳恭惟某官懷覇王之略通天地曰儒文和文憲之一門積善必有慶司業司成之六朔超資曾無難朝未收選席之權衡暮卽授戎門之節鉞制外威名二年魚鳥渾相識安邊功業萬國笙歌醉大平
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 上慶尙安撫使崔司成滋賀正狀
  author: 金之岱
  language: lzh
  text: 雞人報曉。爭糊楚戶之鷄。鳳詔頒春。催浴荀池之鳳。恭惟某官。懷覇王之略。通天地曰儒。文和文憲之一門。積善必有慶。司業司成之六朔。超資曾無難。朝未收選席之權衡。暮卽授戎門之節鉞。制外威名。二年魚鳥渾相識。安邊功業。萬國笙歌醉大平。
korean:
  title: 상 경상안무사 최사성 자 하정 장
  author: 김지대
  language: kor
  text: 계인(鷄人)이 새벽을 알리며 초호(楚戶)의 닭을 못 울게 서두르고, 봉조(鳳詔)가 새봄을 반포하며 순지(荀池)의 봉(鳳)이 목욕을 재촉합니다. 삼가 생각하건대, 모관(某官)은 왕도(王道)와 패도(覇道)를 품은 지략이요, 천문(天文)과 지리(地理)를 통한 선비로서 문화공(文和公)과 문헌공(文憲公)의 한 집안이라 적선(積善)을 하였으니 반드시 경사가 있을 것입니다. 사업(司業)과 사성(司成) 벼슬을 여섯 달 내에 다 지냈으니 승진에 있어서는 일찍이 무난하였으며, 아침에 선석(選席 시험관)의 권형(權衡)을 맡았고, 저물녘에 군문(軍門)의 절월(節鉞 대장)을 받았으니, 외이(外夷)를 제어하신 위엄과 명망은 2년 동안에 어조(魚鳥)까지도 서로 알게 되었고 변방을 안정시킨 공과 업적은 온나라가 노래를 부르며 태평에 취해 있습니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0510_010_0550&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Commendation for Choi Sa-seong, Pacification Commissioner of Gyeongsang Province
  author: Kim Ji-dae
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The rooster-keepers announce the dawn, yet hastily silence the cocks of the southern gates,
    while the phoenix-decree proclaims the new spring, urging the phoenix of Xun Pool to bathe.

    With utmost reverence, I contemplate this official:
    One who carries both the way of the sage-king and the strategy of the hegemon,
    versed in the patterns of heaven and the principles of earth—
    a scholar of the lineage of Master Munhwa and Master Munheon,
    where accumulated virtue surely brings abundant blessings.

    Having served as Director of Studies and Director of Scholars within a mere six months,
    promotion came to him without impediment.
    In the morning, he grasped the scales of the examination; by evening, he received the commander's staff.
    His authority and renown in restraining the outer tribes spread wide—
    within two years, even fish and birds came to recognize his name.
    His achievements in securing the borderlands bear such fruit:
    ten thousand voices sing, and the whole realm dances drunk upon great peace.
  footnotes:
    - The rooster-keepers and phoenix-decree are allusions to imperial officials and authority. Here they reference the official's role in maintaining order and receiving imperial favor.
    - Master Munhwa and Master Munheon refer to esteemed ancestors in Choi Sa-seong's lineage, suggesting inherited virtue and scholarly achievement.
    - The 'scales of examination' and 'commander's staff' represent civil and military authority respectively, indicating rapid advancement through both spheres.
    - The reference to fish and birds recognizing his name is an expression of his influence extending even to the natural world—a traditional poetic hyperbole indicating complete pacification and harmonious governance.
